Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}. Cut @broccoli{1%unit} into bite-size pieces if necessary.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a small #pot over medium-high heat. Add garlic and cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, @water{3/4%cup}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to use in Step 6.

Meanwhile, toss broccoli on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of cooking oil, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

== Salmon ==

While broccoli roasts, pat @salmon{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Season all over with salt and pepper.

> Fish is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

Heat a drizzle of cooking oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add salmon; cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

> If chicken cutlets are on the thicker side, reduce heat to medium and cover; cook 5-7 minutes on second side.

Transfer salmon to a #cutting board{} to rest.

== Sauce ==

Add @apricot jam{1%unit}, @ponzu sauce{12%ml}, @Sriracha{1%tsp}, and @water{1/4%cup} to same pan over medium-high heat. Cook, stirring, until thickened, ~{1-3%minutes}.

> If sauce seems too thick, stir in more water 1 tsp at a time.

Turn off heat and stir in @butter{1%tbsp}. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

== Garlic Rice ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tbsp}. Season with salt and pepper.

== To Serve ==

Slice salmon crosswise on a diagonal.

Divide salmon, broccoli, and rice between plates. Spoon sauce over salmon and serve.